The paper deals with the graph realization problem, which involves determining the coordinates of nodes in a graph given a set of distance measurements. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), scientific computing (cs.NA), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions its application to the molecule problem in structural biology, which falls under the sub-category of computational biology (cs.SI).
